The Catalan numbers are given by the formula: \[ C_n = \frac{1}{n+1} \binom{2n}{n} \] For \( n = 13 \), we need the 12th Catalan number (since we are splitting into two subsequences, the index is \( n-1 \)): \[ C_{12} = \frac{1}{13} \binom{24}{12} \] Calculating this value: \[ C_{12} = \frac{1}{13} \times 2704156 = 207935 \] Thus, the number of permutations of 13 cards that can be picked up in exactly two passes is \(\boxed{207935}\).
